                                         JOHANNESBURG - Police in Limpopo have arrested 31 most wanted suspects and recovered stolen goods worth an estimated value of R3.5 million. The arrests follow tip-offs from community members who alerted the police after noticing suspicious behaviour by one of the suspects. Police say preliminary investigations have revealed that the recovered goods were from Mozambique and were in transit to the Free State. The police's Moatshe Ngoepe says: “The crime intelligence operation has yielded positive results following the arrest of 31 highly wanted suspects for various offences, including car hijacking, house robbery and business robbery.” (Edited by Shimoney Regter)